with tweezers.

77
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:16,540
[Shocking! A Russian man hid a wedding ring inside his belly wound!]

78
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,360
A Russian man

79
00:04:15,670 --> 00:04:18,350
hid his proposal ring

80
00:04:18,350 --> 00:04:19,920
in a wound on his belly

81
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,200
and proposed to his girlfriend?

82
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,120
How could he do this?

83
00:04:25,270 --> 00:04:26,310
How creative.

84
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,670
Lu Fangning!

85
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:32,720
What?

86
00:04:33,230 --> 00:04:34,240
Wait,

87
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,280
you two asked me here

88
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,670
to enjoy your cooking.

89
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:37,470
Where is the food?

90
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,080
In the end,

91
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,030
all I have is an unpeeled apple.

92
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,550
What's going on

93
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:43,640
with you two?

94
00:04:43,790 --> 00:04:44,990
Why are you asking me so many things

95
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:45,830
about proposal now?

96
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:46,750
What happened?

97
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,840
I...

98
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,760
-She has a proposal scene!
-She writes about a proposal!

99
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,760
That made sense.

100
00:05:00,990 --> 00:05:02,400
Ms. Lu.

101
00:05:19,230 --> 00:05:21,920
That came out of nowhere.

102
00:05:22,590 --> 00:05:24,510
Not to mention they gave strange answers.

103
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:28,480
They specifically asked me

104
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:29,790
about proposals…

105
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,870
And Ling Rui…

106
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,430
Didn't I say yes ages ago?

107
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:39,520
This is unnecessary.

108
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,480
I don't need this romantic ceremony.

109
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,680
It's a waste of money.

110
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,830
What should I do?

111
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,590
Welcome home.

112
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,920
What are you doing?

113
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:06,240
I was just searching for some information online.

114
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,190
About what? Let me see it.

115
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,160
It's for the hospital.

116
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:09,910
It's very boring.

117
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:10,750
Let me have a look.

118
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:11,990
There's nothing to see. Let it go.

119
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:13,400
You are acting too suspicious.

120
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,480
-Don't be so stingy!
-I told you.

121
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,520
It's nothing.

122
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,720
Just forget it.

123
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:18,000
Trust me.

124
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:20,630
You're overreacting.

125
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:22,910
Are you messaging someone?

126
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,630
No. Who would I message anyone?

127
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:26,550
Let me see it. Just a sneak peek.

128
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,080
-Listen to me.
-Just let me have a look.

129
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:29,030
Your phone.

130
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:30,070
Phone.

131
00:06:31,310 --> 00:06:32,680
I can check your phone. Give it to me.

132
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:34,310
Your phone is ringing.

133
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,750
Answer the call.

134
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,600
I'll question you later.

135
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,240
Hello?

136
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,000
The police station?

137
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:53,610
[Deer Sing]

138
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,950
What do I know about art parks?

139
00:06:57,230 --> 00:06:57,830
I just mentioned it

140
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,360
to someone

141
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,200
from Ming Cheng,

142
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:01,350
he did the job

143
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:02,080
for me voluntarily.

144
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,070
I won't let Lu Fangning

145
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,720
do business here.

146
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:08,200
Mr. Gao,

147
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,280
did I do a great job?

148
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:12,400
I'm serving justice

149
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:13,750
for both of us.

150
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,240
Very good. Well done.

151
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,270
I didn't expect

152
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:20,910
even when Lu Fangning's gone,

153
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:22,920
she could still help me

154
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:24,510
quell a treacherous

155
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:25,920
employee.

156
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:27,870
Mr. Gao.

157
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:31,360
I was only

158
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,960
trying to find out

159
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,950
who used me as their scapegoat.

160
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,880
Who knows?

161
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,870
Manager Yang, impressive work.

162
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:41,710
You secretly handed over

163
00:07:41,710 --> 00:07:42,720
Deer Sing Group's

164
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,030
outlet and manufacturer

165
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:44,600
tenders

166
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,510
to Ming Cheng.

167
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:49,710
The projects, amounts,

168
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:50,790
and details are all here.

169
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,830
Manager Yang, please have a closer look.

170
00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:53,760
If I wronged you

171
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:54,840
with any of the charges,

172
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:56,030
I could help you

173
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:57,230
reduce the amount of compensation.

174
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:04,960
By the way,

175
00:08:05,830 --> 00:08:07,190
how's your son doing lately?

176
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:10,710
As the saying goes,

177
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:11,750
the fish begins to rot

178
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,360
at the head.

179
00:08:21,590 --> 00:08:22,230
Give HR a call.

180
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:23,350
They can handle the rest.

181
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,760
Fire him, fined him, and make it a public announcement.

182
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:26,760
Do it now.

183
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,950
Don't make me repeat myself.

184
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:29,120
Yes, Mr. Gao.

185
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,190
Those jerks.

186
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,630
How dare they hurt my delicate arm!

187
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:37,880
Fortunately, justice is never late.

188
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,750
They are finally arrested.

189
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:42,659
What's wrong?

190
00:08:43,659 --> 00:08:44,480
They've got caught.

191
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,630
Why do you still look upset?

192
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,950
I'm happy.

193
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,390
And someone else

194
00:08:49,390 --> 00:08:50,590
is going to pay for his medical bill.

195
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,870
It doesn't count as work injuries.

196
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,790
I know you're mean with your words.

197
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,040
You still care about me, right?

198
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:57,640
That's enough. I don't care.

199
00:08:57,790 --> 00:08:59,560
You're worried about my arm, right?

200
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,000
Come on.

201
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:04,270
My arm!

202
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,480
This is the precious arm

203
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,600
that makes you money.

204
00:09:07,830 --> 00:09:08,800
Otherwise,

205
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:09,680
why did you confront

206
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,830
your enemy for me?

207
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,830
However,

208
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,400
I think you got the wrong guy.

209
00:09:20,670 --> 00:09:22,240
I can confront him as I please.

210
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:25,200
I don't need a reason.

211
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:38,070
[It seems like]

212
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:38,750
[you've]

213
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,030
[stooped very low while I was away.]

214
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:41,960
I didn't know

215
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:43,480
you were such a lousy person

216
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,320
who would resort to petty tricks.

217
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:48,990
Do you think

218
00:09:48,990 --> 00:09:49,830
you're the most pitiful

219
00:09:49,830 --> 00:09:51,590
and the greatest person alive?

220
00:09:51,590 --> 00:09:52,430
Is that why you think

221
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:53,190
we must play along

222
00:09:53,190 --> 00:09:54,640
with your overdramatic story?

223
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:11,880
I've warmed some milk for you.

224
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:12,840
Drink it.

225
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:13,680
Thank you.

226
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,760
That's all?

227
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:30,030
What's wrong?

228
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,280
The problems are all solved.

229
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,960
The park is ready for businesses.

230
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,470
Don't worry about it.

231
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,590
Have some rest.

232
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:41,240
I just think

233
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:42,990
I've wronged him.

234
00:10:44,950 --> 00:10:46,040
When did you ever regret

235
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,230
scolding others?

236
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:50,150
I don't

237
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,120
regret it at all!

238
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,990
What I said when I scolded him

239
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:54,750
was all reasonable.

240
00:10:54,790 --> 00:10:55,320
You know that.

241
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,150
I might have been

242
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,280
a little harsh on him.

243
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,710
But essentially, I wasn't wrong.

244
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,280
You're so naughty.

245
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,670
What was that for?

246
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:12,400
Stopping you from overthinking.

247
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:13,750
Especially from

248
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,150
thinking about another man.

249
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:19,960
You consider Gao Erfan a man?

250
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:21,310
You're still thinking about him?

251
00:11:21,310 --> 00:11:22,000
I…

252
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:23,920
What about now?

253
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,430
-And now?
-No. No.

254
00:11:26,950 --> 00:11:27,790
Who should you be thinking?

255
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:30,670
I am

256
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:31,750
thinking about Youyou.

257
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:33,910
Youyou's asleep.

258
00:11:34,550 --> 00:11:35,510
It's useless to think about him.

259
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:38,000
Then…

260
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,240
I'm warning you.

261
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,960
Think carefully before you answer.

262
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:44,240
I think about you.

263
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,840
Are you sure Youyou is asleep?

264
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:23,940
[Gao Erfan]

265
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,510
[I'm Ling Rui.]

266
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:56,390
[Fangning's birthday is two days from now.]

267
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:58,710
[You were the one Lu Yue loved most.]

268
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:00,830
[I hope you could attend the party for her.]

269
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:18,640
This one could do.

270
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:20,150
It's full of bling.

271
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:22,030
It suits Fangning's style.

272
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,040
Sir.

273
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,590
May I help you?

274
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,440
I want to order this cake.

275
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,400
Sorry, sir,

276
00:13:27,230 --> 00:13:31,090
[Blisscake]

277
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,190
we're low in stock of this cake.

278
00:13:29,190 --> 00:13:30,030
Besides, the last one

279
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:31,240
had already been ordered.

280
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,790
Could you make another one?

281
00:13:32,790 --> 00:13:34,630
I'm afraid we can't finish it by tomorrow.

282
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,840
Well, let me explain

283
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:37,760
the situation to you.

284
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,110
My buddy

285
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:39,750
finally

286
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,880
asked me for help.

287
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,160
I must finish the task

288
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:43,000
with perfection.

289
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,510
Otherwise, I would fail him.

290
00:13:44,510 --> 00:13:45,760
Maybe you could

291
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,310
give me the number of the customer

292
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:48,040
who ordered the cake.

293
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,990
I could talk to him.

294
00:13:48,990 --> 00:13:49,990
Maybe he would let me have it.

295
00:13:49,990 --> 00:13:50,800
Sorry, sir.

296
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,950
Our policies forbid us

